1
00:00:06,923 --> 00:00:08,967
[solemn music playing]

2
00:00:13,722 --> 00:00:14,723
[Eun-jung] Are you…

3
00:00:18,893 --> 00:00:20,979
really sick enough to be entertaining

4
00:00:22,439 --> 00:00:24,065
the idea of euthanasia?

5
00:00:24,149 --> 00:00:26,192
[Sang-yeon] It's not just an idea.

6
00:00:28,236 --> 00:00:30,864
It has been decided already.

7
00:00:37,704 --> 00:00:40,874
This place is very strict
in determining who they approve.

8
00:00:41,374 --> 00:00:43,710
I also didn't make this decision lightly.

9
00:00:47,422 --> 00:00:49,883
I would… still go

10
00:00:49,966 --> 00:00:52,802
even if… you declined.

11
00:00:56,222 --> 00:00:57,307
But, uh…

12
00:00:59,517 --> 00:01:00,477
But…

13
00:01:03,396 --> 00:01:06,107
I really hope that you say yes
and come with me.

14
00:01:19,370 --> 00:01:22,040
[Eun-jung] You haven't contacted me
in ten years.

15
00:01:23,416 --> 00:01:24,417
And this is what--

16
00:01:24,501 --> 00:01:26,753
[sighs] If it wasn't as serious as this,

17
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:30,048
how could I have even contacted you?

18
00:01:34,511 --> 00:01:35,512
All I have

19
00:01:37,555 --> 00:01:38,973
is one month left.

20
00:01:39,057 --> 00:01:40,892
And who gave you that deadline?

21
00:01:44,687 --> 00:01:45,897
You did, right?

22
00:01:46,397 --> 00:01:47,649
[Sang-yeon sighs]

23
00:01:50,276 --> 00:01:52,821
- Eun-jung.
- [Eun-jung] You're asking me a favor.

24
00:01:55,406 --> 00:01:57,033
But I'm not gonna say yes.

25
00:02:00,954 --> 00:02:02,622
[Eun-jung gets up]

26
00:02:06,709 --> 00:02:07,836
Also…

27
00:02:10,171 --> 00:02:12,465
it's barbaric to even ask me to do this.

28
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:15,343
Understood?

29
00:02:19,055 --> 00:02:20,098
Ryu Eun-jung.

30
00:02:26,563 --> 00:02:27,939
[pensive music playing]

31
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:30,275
[alarm beeps]

32
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:33,611
[music fades]

33
00:02:35,071 --> 00:02:35,989
[sighs]

34
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:40,118
[cell phone vibrates]

35
00:02:43,496 --> 00:02:45,957
[Choi] <i>Did everything go well</i>
<i>with CEO Cheon?</i>

36
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:48,001
[Eun-jung] <i>Yes,</i>

37
00:02:48,084 --> 00:02:50,628
<i>but I won't be pushing through</i>
<i>with the project.</i>

38
00:02:50,712 --> 00:02:52,797
<i>Let's just find something else to adapt.</i>

39
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:55,008
["Reason" playing]

40
00:02:55,091 --> 00:02:56,134
[sighs]

41
00:02:56,217 --> 00:03:00,263
<i>♪ I'm walking somewhere I don't know ♪</i>

42
00:03:01,222 --> 00:03:05,977
<i>♪ As if there's nothing</i>
<i>I can say for sure ♪</i>

43
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:11,858
<i>♪ There's no time for me to think of it </i>♪

44
00:03:13,359 --> 00:03:17,822
<i>♪ It feels like</i>
<i>I'm being led by something ♪</i>

45
00:03:18,448 --> 00:03:20,158
<i>♪ To the unknown </i>♪

46
00:03:20,241 --> 00:03:22,702
<i>♪ Ooh-ooh ♪</i>

47
00:03:23,244 --> 00:03:26,164
<i>♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh ♪</i>

48
00:03:26,247 --> 00:03:29,167
<i>♪ Ooh-ooh ♪</i>

49
00:03:29,250 --> 00:03:31,085
<i>♪ Ooh-ooh ♪</i>

50
00:03:32,253 --> 00:03:36,174
YOU AND EVERYTHING ELSE

51
00:03:58,071 --> 00:04:02,742
HOW TO DEAL WITH CANCER
WHAT CANCER MEANS TO ME

52
00:04:11,626 --> 00:04:13,419
[cell phone vibrating]

53
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:19,509
Hello?

54
00:04:21,177 --> 00:04:23,471
CERTIFICATE OF REGISTERED ASSETS
PROPERTIES

55
00:04:23,554 --> 00:04:26,641
PROPERTY OWNER
CHEON SANG-YEON

56
00:04:28,643 --> 00:04:29,769
What is this?

57
00:04:29,852 --> 00:04:33,731
Ah well, CEO Cheon will be bequeathing
to you this piece of property.

58
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:36,776
"Bequeathing"?

59
00:04:37,944 --> 00:04:40,655
[man] Oh, yes. You must be surprised.

60
00:04:40,738 --> 00:04:44,242
This property is in Seongsu-dong with
a market price of 13 billion won.

61
00:04:44,325 --> 00:04:46,411
If you look here,
this is the building's exterior.

62
00:04:46,494 --> 00:04:48,079
[chuckles] Beautiful, hmm?

63
00:04:48,162 --> 00:04:49,998
From the rent alone,
this property will give you

64
00:04:50,081 --> 00:04:52,375
a guaranteed monthly income
of 40 million won.

65
00:04:54,836 --> 00:04:58,881
To be honest, I'm kind of jealous.
Lifelong friends do have perks--

66
00:04:58,965 --> 00:05:01,426
You're telling me
that this is the urgent matter?

67
00:05:01,509 --> 00:05:05,805
This is the matter that you made clear
to me you couldn't discuss over the phone?

68
00:05:08,474 --> 00:05:13,021
Ah. I do apologize for making you
take time from your busy schedule.

69
00:05:13,104 --> 00:05:15,023
We can discuss
the important matters later,

70
00:05:15,106 --> 00:05:17,859
but first, I'd like to request a copy
of your resident registration,

71
00:05:17,942 --> 00:05:19,027
if you don't mind.

72
00:05:19,110 --> 00:05:20,695
[phone call ringing]

73
00:05:20,778 --> 00:05:21,696
Uh, ma'am?

74
00:05:22,196 --> 00:05:24,490
[voice mail] <i>The number</i>
<i>you've dialed is unavailable.</i>

75
00:05:25,950 --> 00:05:27,744
Tell me where CEO Cheon is.

76
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:29,829
This is unfortunate.

77
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:33,291
I'm afraid she isn't doing well enough
to receive guests.

78
00:05:33,374 --> 00:05:34,250
[Eun-jung sighs]

79
00:05:36,961 --> 00:05:38,671
How bad's her condition?

80
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:43,926
You can't just barge in like this.

81
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:46,387
I'll talk to her through the door.
Don't worry.

82
00:05:46,888 --> 00:05:48,014
Which room is it?

83
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:58,775
It's me, Eun-jung.

84
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:01,069
Why bother someone

85
00:06:01,152 --> 00:06:03,863
if you can't even show them
how much you've been suffering?

86
00:06:04,614 --> 00:06:06,657
Let's just keep living our separate lives.

87
00:06:07,325 --> 00:06:09,285
I hope that your treatment goes well.

88
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:11,454
Don't contact me again.

89
00:06:19,337 --> 00:06:22,048
<i>I don't know what makes me the most livid.</i>

90
00:06:23,966 --> 00:06:26,302
<i>Was it how rude</i>
<i>the accountant was towards me?</i>

91
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:31,474
<i>Sang-yeon's stubbornness in refusing</i>
<i>to open up to me at her most vulnerable?</i>

92
00:06:33,184 --> 00:06:34,894
<i>Or maybe it's because I feel</i>

93
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:37,605
<i>helpless in this situation.</i>

94
00:06:39,148 --> 00:06:40,483
ELEMENTARY SCHOOL EPISODE

95
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:44,070
THIS SHORT MIDDLE SCHOOL KID WOULD,
THREE YEARS LATER, BECOME MY FIRST LOVE

96
00:06:44,153 --> 00:06:45,405
[Eun-jung] <i>All I can do</i>

97
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:47,156
<i>is write.</i>

98
00:06:49,951 --> 00:06:51,452
<i>I'll face my fears</i>…

99
00:06:51,536 --> 00:06:53,079
1996, SECOND YEAR OF MIDDLE SCHOOL

100
00:06:53,162 --> 00:06:55,206
<i>…and allow this story to unfold.</i>

101
00:06:55,832 --> 00:06:59,627
AT LAST, ON THE CORRIDOR BULLETIN…

102
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:01,712
[children chattering excitedly]

103
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:07,301
[gasps]

104
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:08,803
10TH: RYU EUN-JUNG
AVERAGE SCORE 97.5

105
00:07:08,886 --> 00:07:10,638
[Na-mi] Wow,
tenth place in the whole school?

106
00:07:10,721 --> 00:07:12,515
I can't believe it.

107
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:14,142
- This is crazy!
- This is huge!

108
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:16,185
Ugh, Eun-jung, you're so annoying!

109
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:18,396
[girl 1] I know.
Why do you have to be smart and cool?!

110
00:07:18,479 --> 00:07:19,939
1ST: CHEON SANG-YEON
AVERAGE SCORE 100

111
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:22,525
Oh, what? Impossible.

112
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:25,820
One hundred? That's not cool.

113
00:07:25,903 --> 00:07:27,738
No human gets a hundred average.

114
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:30,700
- [girl 1] You're not a human either, then.
- [Na-mi] Right?

115
00:07:30,783 --> 00:07:33,035
How did you place tenth
in the whole school?

116
00:07:37,248 --> 00:07:39,083
She didn't even bother checking.

117
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:41,669
Think it's because she's so confident?

118
00:07:46,924 --> 00:07:49,385
If you haven't paid for the field trip,
pay now.

119
00:07:50,428 --> 00:07:51,721
[Na-mi] Look what I have.

120
00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:55,099
- Why do you have to copy me?
- [Na-mi] No, H.O.T. is--

121
00:07:55,183 --> 00:07:57,518
- [Eun-jung] Let's compare.
- Sechskies is way better.

122
00:07:57,602 --> 00:08:00,229
This one's kinda weird,
and this one's not H.O.T. enough.

123
00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:02,857
- His face isn't good.
- [Na-mi] Sechskies way better than these.

124
00:08:02,940 --> 00:08:04,525
- Eun Ji-won is like…
- [sighs]

125
00:08:05,026 --> 00:08:06,402
[woman 1] Ms. Jang.

126
00:08:07,028 --> 00:08:08,571
[Ms. Jang] I'm sorry.

127
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:12,200
The gas stove broke down this morning.
I had to get it fixed.

128
00:08:12,283 --> 00:08:13,493
[woman scoffs]

129
00:08:13,576 --> 00:08:15,453
Everyone's got their own problems.

130
00:08:16,287 --> 00:08:19,040
You have until tomorrow
to pay all overdue installments.

131
00:08:19,874 --> 00:08:22,668
I appreciate it. I'm sorry.

132
00:08:27,423 --> 00:08:28,633
[Eun-jung] I'm home.

133
00:08:28,716 --> 00:08:30,384
- You're here, yay!
- Yep.

134
00:08:31,302 --> 00:08:33,471
Did you get your report card today?

135
00:08:35,473 --> 00:08:36,557
What?

136
00:08:37,141 --> 00:08:38,392
Are your grades not good?

137
00:08:44,815 --> 00:08:46,734
[gasps] Ryu Eun-jung!

138
00:08:46,817 --> 00:08:47,860
Oh my God!

139
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:50,696
Oh wow, wow, wow! [gasps]

140
00:08:51,322 --> 00:08:54,784
Is this real!? Since my superstar,
Eun-jung, has come in tenth place--

141
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,244
Don't buy me the computer.

142
00:08:57,411 --> 00:08:58,412
Why not?

143
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:02,583
You were so upset that we were
the only ones without a computer.

144
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:05,878
'Cause, uh, you can buy me
the new model when it's released.

145
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:08,714
All right, but I promised
I'd buy you some--

146
00:09:08,798 --> 00:09:11,050
How about money to buy some clothes?

147
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:13,761
- Clothes?
- Clothes.

148
00:09:13,844 --> 00:09:15,471
For the field trip talent show.

149
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:17,974
["Eve's Warning"
by Park Mi Kyung playing]

150
00:09:18,057 --> 00:09:18,933
[chuckles softly]

151
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:26,107
[in Korean] ♪ <i>If you keep trying</i>
<i>To deceive me </i>♪

152
00:09:26,190 --> 00:09:29,527
♪ <i>Thinking your charm</i>
<i>Is something unique </i>♪

153
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:33,739
♪ <i>I won't have any more love to give-- </i>♪

154
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:38,119
[in English] How come you're so stiff?
You can't do this?

155
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:40,288
- For real?
- It's way too hard.

156
00:09:40,371 --> 00:09:42,373
Let's not do the version
with backup dancers.

157
00:09:42,456 --> 00:09:43,791
What's so hard?

158
00:09:44,458 --> 00:09:46,210
Just move in a circle like this.

159
00:09:48,087 --> 00:09:50,339
Twist your feet out, like this!

160
00:09:51,299 --> 00:09:53,301
- Like this-- Ah!
- [Eun-jung gasps]

161
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:56,053
- Did you get hurt?
- Are you okay?

162
00:09:57,388 --> 00:09:59,849
Who wants to backup dance
"Eve's Warning" with us?

163
00:10:08,816 --> 00:10:09,984
No one does.

164
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:12,570
There's not much time left.

165
00:10:13,738 --> 00:10:15,323
It's my fault.

166
00:10:15,406 --> 00:10:16,490
No it's not.

167
00:10:17,158 --> 00:10:19,285
It's not like you got hurt on purpose.

168
00:10:22,872 --> 00:10:24,498
Will you still do this with me?

169
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:27,209
Just me?

170
00:10:29,253 --> 00:10:30,129
Well…

171
00:10:31,672 --> 00:10:34,925
What about Kang Soo-jee instead?
Her songs don't use backup dancers.

172
00:10:35,676 --> 00:10:38,179
- Kang Soo-jee is--
- Kang Soo-jee's so pretty.

173
00:10:38,262 --> 00:10:40,056
- She's so innocent.
- The best!

174
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:42,850
- You know, Jun-ho probably likes her.
- Mm-hmm.

175
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:46,020
["Violet Fragrance"
by Kang Soo-jee playing]

176
00:10:47,271 --> 00:10:49,357
[in Korean] ♪ <i>The way you approached me </i>♪

177
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:52,902
♪ <i>Like a violet haze… </i>♪

178
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:54,987
- [boys snicker]
- [boy 1, in English] Let's go.

179
00:10:56,072 --> 00:10:57,156
Ugh, I quit.

180
00:10:57,239 --> 00:10:58,991
But I even bought an outfit.

181
00:11:02,411 --> 00:11:03,245
[Sang-yeon] Me.

182
00:11:04,455 --> 00:11:05,289
You?

183
00:11:05,998 --> 00:11:07,249
You, what?

184
00:11:09,251 --> 00:11:10,461
I'll backup dance.

185
00:11:10,544 --> 00:11:13,714
[drumbeat, drumroll]

186
00:11:14,507 --> 00:11:16,801
You'll, um, be a backup dancer?

187
00:11:18,886 --> 00:11:21,347
["Eve's Warning"
by Park Mi Kyung playing]

188
00:11:24,266 --> 00:11:26,519
[audience cheering]

189
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:38,072
CUTIES

190
00:11:44,954 --> 00:11:50,000
[in Korean] ♪ <i>Today, you avoid me again</i>
<i>You're up to no good </i>♪

191
00:11:50,668 --> 00:11:52,253
♪ <i>But I know the truth </i>♪

192
00:11:52,336 --> 00:11:55,965
♪ <i>If you know my feelings for you </i>♪

193
00:11:56,048 --> 00:11:59,677
♪ <i>Don't be a fool</i>
<i>And make any more mistakes </i>♪

194
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:02,680
♪ <i>I, too, feel myself wavering </i>♪

195
00:12:02,763 --> 00:12:06,100
♪ <i>When other great men tempt me </i>♪

196
00:12:06,183 --> 00:12:09,645
♪ <i>If you keep trying to deceive me </i>♪

197
00:12:09,729 --> 00:12:12,815
♪ <i>Thinking your charm</i>
<i>Is something unique </i>♪

198
00:12:12,898 --> 00:12:17,528
♪ <i>I won't have any more love to give you </i>♪

199
00:12:17,611 --> 00:12:23,576
- ♪ <i>I will just walk away </i>♪
- [audience clapping, cheering]

200
00:12:31,041 --> 00:12:32,793
[cheering intensifies]

201
00:12:34,211 --> 00:12:37,548
- [girl 1] One, two, three.
- Hey, do we look amazing in it?

202
00:12:38,549 --> 00:12:41,051
- I wanna see.
- [Eun-jung] Let's see! What else?

203
00:12:41,135 --> 00:12:43,012
- [girl 2] Peace sign!
- Peace sign? Let's do this.

204
00:12:43,095 --> 00:12:44,930
- Do a "v."
- [girl 3] One, two, three.

205
00:12:45,014 --> 00:12:45,848
[shutter clicks]

206
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:48,184
- Hey, Ryu Eun-jung!
- Yeah?

207
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:49,894
- [Na-mi] Are you coming?
- Huh?

208
00:12:49,977 --> 00:12:51,145
I'll be right back.

209
00:12:52,021 --> 00:12:54,148
We have time for another one. What's next?

210
00:12:54,732 --> 00:12:56,358
- [Eun-jung] Let's take one.
- Huh?

211
00:12:56,859 --> 00:12:58,027
[sweet music playing]

212
00:12:58,694 --> 00:13:01,238
- Can you take one for us?
- [Eun-jung] Over here, come here.

213
00:13:06,035 --> 00:13:09,121
[girl 4] On the count of three.
One, two, three.

214
00:13:12,249 --> 00:13:13,375
[music fades]

215
00:13:22,551 --> 00:13:24,553
- [Sang-yeon] What are you doing?
- Huh?

216
00:13:25,054 --> 00:13:26,138
Uh, nothing.

217
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:27,848
[sweet music resumes]

218
00:13:35,481 --> 00:13:37,983
[Sang-yeon] These are my brother's,
so pick whatever.

219
00:13:43,989 --> 00:13:46,909
[adult Eun-jung] <i>I'd never been</i>
<i>in a room like that before.</i>

220
00:13:47,409 --> 00:13:49,912
<i>It was filled with so many things.</i>

221
00:13:55,417 --> 00:13:56,710
[music fades]

222
00:13:57,753 --> 00:13:59,004
[dramatic music playing]

223
00:14:00,923 --> 00:14:01,924
[Eun-jung] Whoa!

224
00:14:02,466 --> 00:14:04,051
How did they make this?

225
00:14:05,594 --> 00:14:08,305
Barry Sonnenfeld
used to be a cinematographer.

226
00:14:09,223 --> 00:14:10,766
Barry… what?

227
00:14:11,475 --> 00:14:12,685
Barry Sonnenfeld.

228
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:18,858
He was a cinematographer before,
so he films things in a unique way.

229
00:14:18,941 --> 00:14:20,818
Do you memorize the names
of all the directors?

230
00:14:20,901 --> 00:14:23,320
Living with Cheon Sang-hak,
you'd be the same way.

231
00:14:24,822 --> 00:14:27,908
- I guess so.
- I think my brother's crazy.

232
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:31,120
He's practically seen
every movie there is.

233
00:14:31,787 --> 00:14:33,914
But somehow he's better in school than me.

234
00:14:34,623 --> 00:14:36,750
He even placed 12th
in the mock college exams.

235
00:14:36,834 --> 00:14:38,794
Twelfth in the whole country, you mean?

236
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:40,546
- Uh-huh.
- [key turning in lock]

237
00:14:42,256 --> 00:14:44,592
- [music stops]
- Oh. Is that Ms. Yoon?

238
00:14:44,675 --> 00:14:46,010
[clattering]

239
00:14:49,597 --> 00:14:52,099
[Eun-jung] Ms. Yoon, how are you?

240
00:14:52,182 --> 00:14:53,183
Oh, Eun-jung!

241
00:14:54,101 --> 00:14:56,729
Wow, you have grown up so much!

242
00:14:56,812 --> 00:14:59,565
I'm giving you a hug
since it's been too long!

243
00:14:59,648 --> 00:15:01,859
Oh my goodness! [chuckles happily]

244
00:15:03,611 --> 00:15:05,279
[dramatic music resumes]

245
00:15:07,323 --> 00:15:08,198
[Ms. Yoon sighs]

246
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:10,409
[chuckles]

247
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:15,789
Is your mom's diner doing well?

248
00:15:15,873 --> 00:15:19,293
She said when the big store opened,
there's been a lot less people.

249
00:15:19,376 --> 00:15:20,836
Oh, that's too bad.

250
00:15:22,254 --> 00:15:25,424
Her <i>sujebi </i>is wonderful.
I should go visit her.

251
00:15:29,136 --> 00:15:30,137
I don't wanna eat this.

252
00:15:31,597 --> 00:15:32,431
Why?

253
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:34,516
Eun-jung, make sure you eat.

254
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,519
And, Sang-yeon,
help yourself when you feel like eating.

255
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:39,271
[Sang-yeon sighs]

256
00:15:39,355 --> 00:15:41,482
- [footsteps approaching]
- [door opens]

257
00:15:43,025 --> 00:15:44,193
- [boy] I'm home.
- [door closes]

258
00:15:44,276 --> 00:15:47,988
Hi! It's Sang-yeon's <i>oppa.</i>
Wash your hands and come eat.

259
00:15:54,703 --> 00:15:56,956
- [Sang-yeon] She's a friend.
- [Ms. Yoon] My former student.

260
00:15:59,667 --> 00:16:01,460
I know. Ryu Eun-jung.

261
00:16:03,671 --> 00:16:06,173
Wait. How do you know her?

262
00:16:07,758 --> 00:16:08,884
We crossed paths.

263
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:12,137
- [Sang-yeon] When was that?
- [Sang-hak] That's too much.

264
00:16:12,221 --> 00:16:13,222
[Ms. Yoon] Okay.

265
00:16:14,848 --> 00:16:15,933
When?

266
00:16:17,476 --> 00:16:19,144
Just, uh… I'll tell ya…

267
00:16:20,145 --> 00:16:21,188
[hushed] …later.

268
00:16:23,273 --> 00:16:25,985
[adult Eun-jung] <i>I never thought</i>
<i>he'd remember that.</i>

269
00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:27,903
[Sang-hak] Excuse me?

270
00:16:30,489 --> 00:16:32,491
Who are… you?

271
00:16:33,617 --> 00:16:37,037
Oh, uh, I'm Ryu Eun-jung.

272
00:16:38,789 --> 00:16:40,124
[Sang-yeon] <i>Eun-jung's going home.</i>

273
00:16:40,207 --> 00:16:41,041
See ya.

274
00:16:41,125 --> 00:16:42,876
- Did you both have fun?
- Yes.

275
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,169
- Have a good night.
- Mm-hmm.

276
00:16:44,253 --> 00:16:45,337
See you tomorrow.

277
00:16:48,757 --> 00:16:50,092
Oh, Eun-jung, one moment.

278
00:16:51,093 --> 00:16:52,845
- [knocking on door]
- [Sang-hak] Yes?

279
00:16:53,804 --> 00:16:56,640
[Ms. Yoon] t's getting late.
Why don't you walk Eun-jung home?

280
00:16:56,724 --> 00:16:59,601
Uh, it's okay.
It's all right for me to go alone.

281
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:01,687
[Ms. Yoon] It's getting late. Take her.

282
00:17:04,648 --> 00:17:06,316
[tender music playing]

283
00:17:15,826 --> 00:17:17,619
<i>Oppa, </i>I'm good.

284
00:17:18,620 --> 00:17:20,080
You can go now.

285
00:17:21,081 --> 00:17:22,708
Which way's your house?

286
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:27,379
[hesitantly] Over there…

287
00:17:27,463 --> 00:17:29,465
[lyrics in Korean]

288
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:33,218
You really don't have to walk me.

289
00:17:33,302 --> 00:17:36,388
It's not even that dark outside.
I'm not scared.

290
00:17:37,347 --> 00:17:41,185
[adult Eun-jung] <i>Our landlord's gate had</i>
<i>a side door that led to where we lived.</i>

291
00:17:41,268 --> 00:17:42,436
<i>I hated it.</i>

292
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:46,273
<i>In those days,</i>
<i>it was the thing that I hated the most.</i>

293
00:17:47,024 --> 00:17:48,776
<i>I lived in a semi-basement.</i>

294
00:17:48,859 --> 00:17:51,361
<i>I never wanted anyone</i>
<i>to see me use that door.</i>

295
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:54,281
- [Sang-hak] How's Sang-yeon these days?
- What?

296
00:17:54,990 --> 00:17:55,908
Sang-yeon?

297
00:17:56,992 --> 00:17:59,286
She's always doing amazing at school.

298
00:18:01,121 --> 00:18:04,500
But I think there's
a lot more to her than just school.

299
00:18:05,542 --> 00:18:09,213
She's the smartest kid that I know,
and she knows a lot about the world.

300
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:11,381
[Sang-hak] Oh yeah?

301
00:18:12,591 --> 00:18:13,842
She knows so much.

302
00:18:14,343 --> 00:18:16,845
And besides all that,
she's a great dancer.

303
00:18:18,222 --> 00:18:19,848
Sang-yeon's a great dancer?

304
00:18:21,308 --> 00:18:23,143
Yes, she's so good.

305
00:18:29,149 --> 00:18:31,777
Which major are you interested in?

306
00:18:32,569 --> 00:18:33,946
I like photography.

307
00:18:34,988 --> 00:18:36,949
- Photography?
- Mm.

308
00:18:37,574 --> 00:18:40,202
- If I get accepted, of course.
- Wow.

309
00:18:42,162 --> 00:18:43,038
What?

310
00:18:44,832 --> 00:18:46,917
[Eun-jung] I expected
something more traditional.

311
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,086
Just because you're so good in school.

312
00:18:49,962 --> 00:18:52,005
[Sang-hak] What would you consider
"more traditional"?

313
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:58,595
Well, it would be
something more like law or medicine…

314
00:19:04,977 --> 00:19:07,354
Oh, yeah.
I have to buy something at the store.

315
00:19:08,105 --> 00:19:12,067
You can go home because…
I'm gonna buy something.

316
00:19:13,443 --> 00:19:14,278
Okay.

317
00:19:16,446 --> 00:19:19,032
No, I meant that you should go.

318
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:24,371
It's gonna take me a while.
Like, a long time. I have so much to buy.

319
00:19:24,454 --> 00:19:26,248
[clicks tongue] I don't mind.

320
00:19:32,754 --> 00:19:39,428
DAJEONG SUPERMARKET

321
00:19:41,096 --> 00:19:43,140
[chimes tinkling]

322
00:19:54,902 --> 00:19:56,069
[camera shutter clicks]

323
00:19:58,530 --> 00:19:59,781
[Eun-jung] What are you doing?

324
00:20:02,492 --> 00:20:03,493
[Sang-hak] Nothing.

325
00:20:05,329 --> 00:20:07,039
This alley is really pretty.

326
00:20:10,626 --> 00:20:12,044
There's nothing pretty about it.

327
00:20:13,420 --> 00:20:14,421
But there is.

328
00:20:14,922 --> 00:20:16,131
[winds camera]

329
00:20:17,132 --> 00:20:19,176
It wouldn't be pretty if you lived here.

330
00:20:20,344 --> 00:20:21,470
You won't get it.

331
00:20:26,308 --> 00:20:27,726
<i>Oppa, </i>please leave.

332
00:20:28,393 --> 00:20:30,354
I've been trying to drop you hints.

333
00:20:36,193 --> 00:20:37,027
Ah…

334
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,154
Sure.

335
00:20:40,739 --> 00:20:42,491
Right, you were.

336
00:20:42,991 --> 00:20:43,909
Yeah.

337
00:20:45,369 --> 00:20:47,162
You should be good from here.

338
00:20:49,998 --> 00:20:51,124
Good night.

339
00:20:54,461 --> 00:20:55,545
Wait a sec.

340
00:21:01,218 --> 00:21:03,720
I, um… apologize.

341
00:21:06,431 --> 00:21:08,433
For saying your neighborhood is pretty

342
00:21:09,142 --> 00:21:11,103
without knowing its history and

343
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:13,397
taking pictures of it.

344
00:21:17,943 --> 00:21:19,069
It's all right.

345
00:21:22,823 --> 00:21:26,076
I should… be the one who should apologize.

346
00:21:27,661 --> 00:21:29,246
I'm kinda embarrassed.

347
00:21:29,746 --> 00:21:31,248
[gentle music playing]

348
00:21:32,708 --> 00:21:35,752
People think I'm always so confident.

349
00:21:40,090 --> 00:21:41,258
I'm the same.

350
00:21:44,970 --> 00:21:47,180
There's things I don't show others

351
00:21:48,056 --> 00:21:49,808
or let people know.

352
00:21:49,891 --> 00:21:51,727
I keep them all to myself.

353
00:21:52,602 --> 00:21:53,687
[Eun-jung] You do?

354
00:21:56,106 --> 00:21:58,483
You mean that… you hide things too?

355
00:21:58,567 --> 00:21:59,776
A lot of things.

356
00:22:00,610 --> 00:22:02,029
Super…

357
00:22:02,112 --> 00:22:04,823
super-duper… lots.

358
00:22:06,199 --> 00:22:07,743
"Super-duper lots"?

359
00:22:09,411 --> 00:22:10,579
Mm-hmm.

360
00:22:13,665 --> 00:22:15,375
Would you like to take a look?

361
00:22:15,876 --> 00:22:18,045
[tender music playing]

362
00:22:24,134 --> 00:22:25,344
[winds camera]

363
00:22:32,267 --> 00:22:34,728
[adult Eun-jung] <i>It was</i>
<i>a strange experience.</i>

364
00:22:35,687 --> 00:22:37,606
<i>The alley through this lens…</i>

365
00:22:39,733 --> 00:22:41,068
<i>was beautiful.</i>

366
00:22:42,569 --> 00:22:43,945
<i>It was a lie.</i>

367
00:22:45,906 --> 00:22:47,115
[Eun-jung] It's pretty.

368
00:22:52,454 --> 00:22:56,249
I'm glad that I'm not the only one
who sees its beauty.

369
00:23:00,337 --> 00:23:01,630
[music intensifies]

370
00:23:36,415 --> 00:23:37,916
[music continues]

371
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:43,422
[music softens]

372
00:23:43,505 --> 00:23:45,924
Don't you think
that Ms. Yoon is really lucky?

373
00:23:47,384 --> 00:23:48,969
If I got you a tutor,

374
00:23:49,052 --> 00:23:51,888
do you think you could get into SNU
and make me proud?

375
00:23:52,472 --> 00:23:54,474
What kind of tutor?

376
00:23:56,143 --> 00:23:57,352
An SNU student.

377
00:23:57,436 --> 00:23:59,479
CONGRATULATIONS CHEON SANG-HAK
ILYEONG HIGH THIRD-YEAR

378
00:23:59,563 --> 00:24:02,399
[adult Eun-jung] <i>Sang-hak </i>oppa
<i>wasn't allowed to pursue photography.</i>

379
00:24:02,482 --> 00:24:03,859
ACCEPTED TO SNU
BUSINESS MANAGEMENT

380
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:06,611
Sang-yeon's <i>oppa</i>?

381
00:24:07,154 --> 00:24:09,573
- [inhales deeply] Hmm…
- [music fades]

382
00:24:12,993 --> 00:24:15,412
My <i>oppa</i>'s weird now. Don't be surprised.

383
00:24:16,496 --> 00:24:18,999
What? Your <i>oppa</i>'s weird?

384
00:24:19,499 --> 00:24:21,126
He doesn't really talk a lot.

385
00:24:21,626 --> 00:24:22,711
I mean, he never did,

386
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:24,629
but right before he went to college,

387
00:24:24,713 --> 00:24:26,756
he mentioned wanting
to major in photography,

388
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:30,218
and it made my dad really mad,
so now he only answers "yes" or "no."

389
00:24:31,052 --> 00:24:34,598
- Then, how's he gonna tutor us?
- That's gonna be fine.

390
00:24:34,681 --> 00:24:36,308
He's getting paid to teach us.

391
00:24:36,391 --> 00:24:39,102
What I meant was
he won't talk about anything else.

392
00:24:39,686 --> 00:24:40,520
Oh…

393
00:24:41,354 --> 00:24:43,356
Wait, is that a new shirt?

394
00:24:45,275 --> 00:24:46,109
Yeah.

395
00:24:47,402 --> 00:24:49,988
- I just thought it looked pretty.
- Oh, it does.

396
00:24:51,490 --> 00:24:53,283
- [knocking on door]
- [door opens]

397
00:24:54,659 --> 00:24:57,120
- Hi, nice to see you.
- [door closes]

398
00:24:59,080 --> 00:24:59,998
[chuckles]

399
00:25:03,668 --> 00:25:05,545
Let's start with the first unit.

400
00:25:06,922 --> 00:25:08,965
Polynomials and factorization.

401
00:25:11,176 --> 00:25:13,553
Factorization will be first.

402
00:25:17,474 --> 00:25:18,517
9 MONTHS LATER
AUTUMN 1997

403
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:22,103
The Korean language test was so hard.
Who comes up with questions like that?

404
00:25:22,187 --> 00:25:23,188
[Sang-yeon] I know.

405
00:25:23,813 --> 00:25:25,649
- Want some toast?
- [Eun-jung] Yeah.

406
00:25:30,904 --> 00:25:35,033
I, um… I got the math questions right
and one wrong in English,

407
00:25:35,116 --> 00:25:37,452
Korean language wasn't great.

408
00:25:37,536 --> 00:25:40,247
Sang-yeon did so good
and basically only got one wrong.

409
00:25:56,388 --> 00:25:58,723
[Sang-hak] I see why
this might've been tricky.

410
00:25:59,224 --> 00:26:02,894
Number two makes sense as the answer,
but five is also correct.

411
00:26:04,229 --> 00:26:07,440
I think it would be fair to describe
the character as pessimistic as well.

412
00:26:10,610 --> 00:26:12,362
Ah. This word.

413
00:26:12,946 --> 00:26:13,947
Do you know it?

414
00:26:15,740 --> 00:26:16,992
"Pessimistic."

415
00:26:18,493 --> 00:26:20,704
No, I've never heard of it.

416
00:26:22,080 --> 00:26:24,874
It uses the characters
"to hate" and "the world."

417
00:26:24,958 --> 00:26:27,377
Combined,
it's "to grow weary of the world."

418
00:26:27,460 --> 00:26:30,213
In other words,
it means someone who is pessimistic.

419
00:26:31,631 --> 00:26:32,549
Ah…

420
00:26:33,383 --> 00:26:34,551
Pessimistic.

421
00:26:38,138 --> 00:26:39,848
[peppy music playing]

422
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:53,528
"To grow weary… of the world."

423
00:26:56,573 --> 00:26:57,449
[girl 1] Here!

424
00:26:59,326 --> 00:27:01,161
Ooh. Whatcha doing?

425
00:27:02,829 --> 00:27:04,914
I think I'm too pessimistic.

426
00:27:06,166 --> 00:27:07,292
Pest… what?

427
00:27:07,834 --> 00:27:08,710
[girl 2] Whoa!

428
00:27:09,586 --> 00:27:13,131
I didn't say "pest." I said "pessimistic."

429
00:27:14,549 --> 00:27:17,802
- [Na-mi] What's that mean?
- It's two characters put together.

430
00:27:17,886 --> 00:27:20,055
"To hate" put together with "the world."

431
00:27:21,306 --> 00:27:23,600
Hmm, okay.

432
00:27:24,309 --> 00:27:27,228
Let's go to Ju-eun's later
to watch <i>Men in Black </i>together.

433
00:27:29,230 --> 00:27:31,149
[chuckles softly] Yeah, okay.

434
00:27:34,527 --> 00:27:36,279
[adult Eun-jung] <i>No one understood.</i>

435
00:27:37,405 --> 00:27:39,991
<i>But whether I could</i>
<i>explain it correctly or not,</i>

436
00:27:41,117 --> 00:27:42,494
<i>I used that word…</i>

437
00:27:42,577 --> 00:27:43,662
The pen won't work.

438
00:27:43,745 --> 00:27:45,205
<i>…whenever I got the chance.</i>

439
00:27:45,288 --> 00:27:46,247
Use mine.

440
00:27:46,331 --> 00:27:50,126
- The tip pops out on those pens.
- [Ju-eun] That happened to mine too.

441
00:27:50,210 --> 00:27:53,296
- [Na-mi] Really?
- [Ju-eun] Yeah, but Monami pens are good.

442
00:27:54,214 --> 00:27:55,632
Blue's all you're gonna get?

443
00:27:55,715 --> 00:27:58,051
Blue can mean that you're sad.

444
00:27:58,134 --> 00:27:59,260
[Ju-eun] Are you sad?

445
00:27:59,761 --> 00:28:02,514
- I'm just too pessimistic.
- [Ju-eun] "Pessimistic"?

446
00:28:03,014 --> 00:28:06,142
[Na-mi] Whatever.
She keeps talking about being a pest.

447
00:28:06,226 --> 00:28:08,436
[Eun-jung] It's not "pest."
It's "pessimistic."

448
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:10,647
"To hate" put together with "the world."

449
00:28:11,314 --> 00:28:13,858
- I'm a pessimistic person.
- Whatever.

450
00:28:14,734 --> 00:28:15,819
That's what I am.

451
00:28:19,531 --> 00:28:20,990
- [music fades]
- [door opens]

452
00:28:22,951 --> 00:28:25,161
- [door closes]
- Sang-yeon's in the bathroom.

