00:30:21,319 --> 00:30:24,948
She, uh… she considers herself
a pessimistic person.

486
00:30:25,532 --> 00:30:26,866
- She said that?
- Mm-hmm.

487
00:30:26,950 --> 00:30:29,744
So I asked her
if there was anything she liked.

488
00:30:30,578 --> 00:30:33,206
She came up with
an endless list of things.

489
00:30:33,706 --> 00:30:36,167
She says she considers
herself a pessimist…

490
00:30:36,251 --> 00:30:38,545
[chuckling] …but she loves so many things.

491
00:30:39,796 --> 00:30:42,924
I keep thinking about it.
It makes me laugh every time.

492
00:30:46,052 --> 00:30:48,680
That's what makes you laugh?

493
00:30:49,514 --> 00:30:51,057
[Sang-hak] Mm-hmm. [chuckles]

494
00:30:58,106 --> 00:30:59,107
Eun-jung.

495
00:31:00,233 --> 00:31:02,277
Oh. Hello.

496
00:31:09,659 --> 00:31:12,328
Sang-yeon and I are gonna
get some <i>tteokbokki.</i>

497
00:31:13,454 --> 00:31:14,998
Where are you coming from?

498
00:31:21,462 --> 00:31:23,882
I just bought a new camera. Wanna see?

499
00:31:26,843 --> 00:31:27,760
Yeah.

500
00:31:28,386 --> 00:31:29,596
A Leica.

501
00:31:32,056 --> 00:31:34,100
- It's called "Leica"?
- Mm-hmm.

502
00:31:34,767 --> 00:31:36,769
It's the company
that makes the cameras.

503
00:31:37,604 --> 00:31:39,939
Oh. It's pretty.

504
00:31:40,523 --> 00:31:42,233
It's pretty like a girl's name.

505
00:31:44,736 --> 00:31:45,653
Eun-jung.

506
00:31:46,863 --> 00:31:50,533
There was once a dog named Laika.
Do you maybe know the story?

507
00:31:52,535 --> 00:31:53,578
I don't.

508
00:31:54,996 --> 00:31:59,083
The Russians used to…
conduct space research.

509
00:31:59,584 --> 00:32:03,546
Instead of a human,
they sent a dog out into space.

510
00:32:04,088 --> 00:32:05,924
And that dog was named Laika.

511
00:32:06,716 --> 00:32:08,593
- Outer space?
- Mm-hmm.

512
00:32:09,677 --> 00:32:10,762
What happened to it?

513
00:32:13,348 --> 00:32:16,309
Well, it never managed
to return, actually.

514
00:32:17,268 --> 00:32:19,187
Oh, that's sad.

515
00:32:20,980 --> 00:32:22,857
It must've been really scared.

516
00:32:26,736 --> 00:32:27,612
Maybe.

517
00:32:34,953 --> 00:32:37,914
Yeah, but you have so many cameras.
Why another one?

518
00:32:39,290 --> 00:32:43,086
Well, I've always wanted
this one the most.

519
00:32:43,628 --> 00:32:44,545
Oh.

520
00:32:45,463 --> 00:32:47,882
<i>Oppa</i>, you like taking pictures that much?

521
00:32:50,134 --> 00:32:51,010
Mm.

522
00:32:54,055 --> 00:32:55,765
When I take photos…

523
00:32:57,850 --> 00:33:00,311
it puts my whole mind at ease.

524
00:33:01,354 --> 00:33:03,106
How does it make it do that?

525
00:33:04,315 --> 00:33:05,441
You're curious?

526
00:33:12,949 --> 00:33:13,866
Look.

527
00:33:15,493 --> 00:33:17,912
This photo was taken
at a shutter speed of 1/60,

528
00:33:17,996 --> 00:33:21,416
which means one sixtieth of a second
is captured in this photograph.

529
00:33:22,583 --> 00:33:24,585
It appears to be a still photo,

530
00:33:24,669 --> 00:33:28,506
but it's actually capturing
1/60th of a second of movement.

531
00:33:30,091 --> 00:33:33,386
Taking photographs is like
collecting time, essentially.

532
00:33:33,928 --> 00:33:35,888
Although they capture
just a glimpse in time,

533
00:33:35,972 --> 00:33:38,391
right there, in that moment is the truth.

534
00:33:39,767 --> 00:33:43,396
However, sometimes
a photo can be misleading.

535
00:33:44,188 --> 00:33:46,524
Since they capture only a fleeting moment,

536
00:33:46,607 --> 00:33:49,819
sometimes what seems true
may not be the whole story.

537
00:33:49,902 --> 00:33:50,737
[Eun-jung] Hmm.

538
00:33:52,572 --> 00:33:54,991
What do you think? Is it interesting?

539
00:33:55,658 --> 00:33:56,993
Absolutely.

540
00:33:57,076 --> 00:33:59,704
Will you teach me
how to take pictures later?

541
00:34:03,332 --> 00:34:04,417
You got it.

542
00:34:08,087 --> 00:34:09,756
[chuckling in distance]

543
00:34:11,799 --> 00:34:13,176
What do you think? Pretty?

544
00:34:13,259 --> 00:34:14,802
[Eun-jung] Yeah, so nice.

545
00:34:25,938 --> 00:34:28,024
- [Sang-yeon] What are you doing?
- You're here.

546
00:34:28,941 --> 00:34:30,443
<i>Oppa </i>showed me his camera.

547
00:34:31,194 --> 00:34:33,613
- You bought another one?
- Have a great time.

548
00:34:33,696 --> 00:34:34,781
[Eun-jung] Bye.

549
00:34:40,411 --> 00:34:42,080
I should've asked him to come.

550
00:34:42,872 --> 00:34:44,499
Does he not like <i>tteokbokki</i>?

551
00:34:45,750 --> 00:34:47,335
You asked him to show you?

552
00:34:48,503 --> 00:34:49,420
[Eun-jung] Hmm?

553
00:34:49,504 --> 00:34:50,671
The camera.

554
00:34:51,506 --> 00:34:55,760
Oh. He told me he just bought it
and asked if I wanted to see it.

555
00:34:56,594 --> 00:34:58,805
He said he'd teach me
how to take pictures.

556
00:34:59,764 --> 00:35:03,518
He always talks about interesting stuff.
He speaks in the most unique way!

557
00:35:03,601 --> 00:35:06,479
How come you told me he never talks?
He speaks fine to me.

558
00:35:06,562 --> 00:35:07,814
Okay, so,

559
00:35:08,856 --> 00:35:11,609
you think my brother talks to you
because you're special?

560
00:35:14,737 --> 00:35:16,531
Hey. What's wrong?

561
00:35:17,198 --> 00:35:18,282
You're being funny.

562
00:35:19,617 --> 00:35:21,285
How am I being funny?

563
00:35:21,369 --> 00:35:24,580
Do you really think you're pessimistic?

564
00:35:26,457 --> 00:35:28,709
Well, that's random. Why bring that up?

565
00:35:28,793 --> 00:35:31,546
You've been telling everybody that
for no reason.

566
00:35:31,629 --> 00:35:33,965
You're too simpleminded
to ever be pessimistic.

567
00:35:36,217 --> 00:35:37,218
Hey!

568
00:35:38,636 --> 00:35:40,847
You have no idea what my mind is like.

569
00:35:40,930 --> 00:35:43,808
If I'm simpleminded, or complex,
or pessimistic, you would never know--

570
00:35:43,891 --> 00:35:45,017
You like my brother.

571
00:35:45,101 --> 00:35:46,602
[tense music playing]

572
00:35:49,230 --> 00:35:51,315
- No, I don't.
- Oh, come on.

573
00:35:51,399 --> 00:35:54,527
I don't. Okay? You should listen
when someone tells you the truth.

574
00:35:54,610 --> 00:35:55,611
[Sang-yeon] Okay, fine.

575
00:35:56,362 --> 00:35:58,114
Well, he already has a girlfriend.

576
00:36:00,158 --> 00:36:03,995
There's no chance even if you do like him.
Keep reminding yourself that.

577
00:36:07,373 --> 00:36:09,000
- [tender music playing]
- Hey!

578
00:36:09,667 --> 00:36:10,501
[sighs]

579
00:36:24,682 --> 00:36:26,642
<i>Oppa</i>, do you have lead refills?

580
00:36:31,063 --> 00:36:32,064
[Sang-yeon sighs]

581
00:36:43,159 --> 00:36:44,035
[clicks pen]

582
00:36:52,835 --> 00:36:55,254
- [Ms. Yoon] Did you have a good session?
- Yes. Goodbye, ma'am.

583
00:36:55,338 --> 00:36:58,841
Oh, don't go, Eun-jung.
We ordered pizza. Eat some before you go.

584
00:36:58,925 --> 00:37:00,509
It's okay. I'm not hungry.

585
00:37:02,637 --> 00:37:04,430
[door opens, closes]

586
00:37:05,056 --> 00:37:07,391
All right. Get home safe, mm?

587
00:37:09,268 --> 00:37:11,270
- Take care.
- [Eun-jung] Have a good night.

588
00:37:17,276 --> 00:37:18,986
She's the worst person ever.

589
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:27,453
Why did you not say goodbye
to your friend?

590
00:37:29,330 --> 00:37:33,000
She didn't say goodbye to me either.
Why are you getting mad at me?

591
00:37:33,084 --> 00:37:35,753
Eun-jung is a guest in our home,
but you live here.

592
00:37:38,381 --> 00:37:40,633
Whatever. I have an exam tomorrow.

593
00:37:40,716 --> 00:37:42,134
Cheon Sang-yeon!

594
00:37:43,427 --> 00:37:46,347
You always say goodbye
with that smug face from the couch.

595
00:37:46,430 --> 00:37:49,976
If your friend is leaving, you should
open the door for her, at the very least.

596
00:37:50,059 --> 00:37:51,394
Being good in studies isn't--

597
00:37:51,477 --> 00:37:53,062
If you like her so much…

598
00:37:55,523 --> 00:37:57,066
make her your daughter, then.

599
00:37:58,109 --> 00:37:59,485
Problem solved.

600
00:38:00,069 --> 00:38:01,570
- What?
- [door opens]

601
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:05,449
You're so annoying.

602
00:38:07,952 --> 00:38:10,830
- [Ms. Yoon] Oh. Cheon Sang-yeon!
- [door slams]

603
00:38:16,335 --> 00:38:18,045
[pager ringing]

604
00:38:35,521 --> 00:38:37,231
Come on, pick up the phone.

605
00:38:37,315 --> 00:38:38,524
[indistinct chattering]

606
00:38:42,570 --> 00:38:43,738
[teacher] Hey, kids!

607
00:38:43,821 --> 00:38:45,156
[kids] Hello!

608
00:38:45,239 --> 00:38:47,033
Wow. The line's freaking long.

609
00:38:47,116 --> 00:38:48,617
Ms. Yoon just paged me.

610
00:38:48,701 --> 00:38:51,579
She's Sang-yeon's mom,
and Sang-yeon skipped school today.

611
00:38:51,662 --> 00:38:53,122
That's probably why.

612
00:38:54,081 --> 00:38:55,124
She skipped?

613
00:38:55,791 --> 00:38:57,501
- We have an exam.
- [Ju-eun] I know.

614
00:38:57,585 --> 00:39:01,047
Our teacher called her house earlier,
but they said she left already.

615
00:39:02,006 --> 00:39:03,341
Maybe she ran away.

616
00:39:03,883 --> 00:39:04,884
Ran away?

617
00:39:06,385 --> 00:39:08,054
[indistinct chattering]

618
00:39:10,681 --> 00:39:12,058
[pager ringing]

619
00:39:17,563 --> 00:39:18,522
[ringing stops]

620
00:39:22,860 --> 00:39:23,944
[girl 1] I'm serious.

621
00:39:24,028 --> 00:39:26,155
[girl 2] He's cute.
Let's go check him out.

622
00:39:26,238 --> 00:39:27,823
- [girl 1 laughs]
- [girl 2] Look.

623
00:39:27,907 --> 00:39:28,949
[girl 3 whistles]

624
00:39:29,033 --> 00:39:32,411
She just ignored me.
Like a stuck-up princess or something.

625
00:39:32,495 --> 00:39:34,121
[pensive music playing]

626
00:39:40,753 --> 00:39:43,005
- [video game beeping]
- [sighs] You're gonna die!

627
00:39:43,089 --> 00:39:44,423
- Hurry up and attack.
- I got it.

628
00:39:44,507 --> 00:39:47,259
- [girl 4] Oh no! I'm losing!
- [girl 5] Right? I knew so.

629
00:39:53,224 --> 00:39:54,183
Welcome.

630
00:39:59,730 --> 00:40:01,941
- [Eun-jung] <i>Hey, where the heck are you?</i>
<i>- </i>[rain pattering]

631
00:40:02,024 --> 00:40:03,526
<i>Did you really run away?</i>

632
00:40:03,609 --> 00:40:05,486
<i>Why aren't you checking your pager?</i>

633
00:40:05,569 --> 00:40:06,445
[sighs]

634
00:40:11,033 --> 00:40:12,743
[girl 3] You're really pretty.

635
00:40:12,827 --> 00:40:14,036
How much do you have?

636
00:40:23,671 --> 00:40:26,882
[Eun-jung] Hey, I've paged you,
like, a hundred times. [sighs]

637
00:40:28,342 --> 00:40:29,760
Where the heck are you at?

638
00:40:31,470 --> 00:40:32,763
[pager beeping]

639
00:40:34,682 --> 00:40:35,683
[beeping stops]

640
00:40:53,659 --> 00:40:54,660
[sighs]

641
00:40:58,831 --> 00:40:59,665
Hey.

642
00:41:04,211 --> 00:41:05,421
You're unbelievable.

643
00:41:06,422 --> 00:41:07,256
[sighs]

644
00:41:07,923 --> 00:41:08,841
I got

645
00:41:10,092 --> 00:41:11,010
mugged.

646
00:41:17,224 --> 00:41:18,225
[Eun-jung sighs]

647
00:41:18,309 --> 00:41:20,478
["You" playing]

648
00:41:21,979 --> 00:41:24,064
Have some so you don't get sick.

649
00:41:24,148 --> 00:41:27,234
<i>♪ I'm singing a song ♪</i>

650
00:41:27,318 --> 00:41:28,402
<i>♪ Flowers bloom… </i>♪

651
00:41:28,486 --> 00:41:30,821
Eat it. My mom's <i>sujebi'</i>s good.

652
00:41:35,326 --> 00:41:36,452
[Ms. Jang] Here.

653
00:41:37,286 --> 00:41:39,872
What's wrong?
You told me you were starving.

654
00:41:40,915 --> 00:41:42,249
Um… I, uh, can't…

655
00:41:43,083 --> 00:41:44,752
I can't pay for any of this.

656
00:41:45,336 --> 00:41:46,962
I can tomorrow though.

657
00:41:48,464 --> 00:41:50,174
[laughs]

658
00:41:51,342 --> 00:41:54,261
Sang-yeon, you're not paying for that.

659
00:41:54,345 --> 00:41:55,471
I'm not?

660
00:41:56,347 --> 00:41:58,724
Do I pay for the meals
when I eat at your place?

661
00:41:59,350 --> 00:42:00,351
Uh…

662
00:42:00,434 --> 00:42:02,728
I mean, this is a restaurant.

663
00:42:03,896 --> 00:42:06,982
It's a restaurant,
but it's still your friend's.

664
00:42:07,066 --> 00:42:07,900
Right, Mom?

665
00:42:07,983 --> 00:42:10,736
Of course. Eat. You must be hungry.

666
00:42:13,572 --> 00:42:15,115
Thank you. I appreciate it.

667
00:42:16,700 --> 00:42:17,701
[Ms. Jang] Ah.

668
00:42:18,661 --> 00:42:22,581
I thought you were just a good student,
but you're adorable.

669
00:42:23,374 --> 00:42:25,960
Sang-yeon, make sure
whenever you get hungry,

670
00:42:26,043 --> 00:42:27,962
you remember that you're welcome here.

671
00:42:28,045 --> 00:42:30,172
When you don't have money,
come right away.

672
00:42:30,673 --> 00:42:32,091
- Understand?
- [sniffles]

673
00:42:35,719 --> 00:42:36,595
[sniffling]

674
00:42:38,222 --> 00:42:39,223
Hey.

675
00:42:45,563 --> 00:42:46,564
Thank you.

676
00:42:58,367 --> 00:43:00,202
This is it. My house.

677
00:43:18,053 --> 00:43:20,806
Are you sure about opening this?

678
00:43:21,307 --> 00:43:22,641
Do I have a choice?

679
00:43:22,725 --> 00:43:25,561
You don't have money,
and you're too stubborn to go home.

680
00:43:26,228 --> 00:43:30,107
Your only option's a public bathhouse,
so I'll give you money.

681
00:43:30,190 --> 00:43:32,651
[sighs gratefully] I'll pay you back.

682
00:43:33,402 --> 00:43:34,403
You better.

683
00:43:34,903 --> 00:43:37,072
You have to buy me a new piggy bank too.

684
00:43:37,698 --> 00:43:38,741
[chuckles]

685
00:43:43,746 --> 00:43:46,665
You're the first person… I invited over.

686
00:43:47,249 --> 00:43:49,793
- Stop lying.
- Why would I be lying about that?

687
00:43:51,253 --> 00:43:54,214
Because you have lots of friends.
You hang out a lot.

688
00:43:54,298 --> 00:43:57,259
I do, but no one's been invited over.

689
00:43:58,177 --> 00:43:59,053
Why?

690
00:44:01,430 --> 00:44:02,598
I'm embarrassed.

691
00:44:03,724 --> 00:44:04,767
About what?

692
00:44:06,935 --> 00:44:09,480
[sighs] You're really dense sometimes.

693
00:44:10,272 --> 00:44:12,191
I'm living in a semi-basement.

694
00:44:13,233 --> 00:44:14,109
Ah.

695
00:44:15,110 --> 00:44:16,111
I get it.

696
00:44:17,237 --> 00:44:20,115
I mean, I shouldn't really
be embarrassed about it,

697
00:44:21,033 --> 00:44:22,701
but I can't help it.

698
00:44:23,577 --> 00:44:24,953
Stupid, right?

699
00:44:33,337 --> 00:44:34,546
My mom, like…

700
00:44:35,839 --> 00:44:36,674
[sniffles]

701
00:44:37,591 --> 00:44:38,967
…hates me, you know.

702
00:44:39,468 --> 00:44:40,302
What?

703
00:44:41,220 --> 00:44:43,972
My mom… hates my guts.

704
00:44:44,056 --> 00:44:45,474
Don't be stupid.

705
00:44:46,767 --> 00:44:49,645
Don't believe me, then.
But it's still true.

706
00:44:51,146 --> 00:44:52,356
[distant clattering]

707
00:44:53,440 --> 00:44:55,150
Uh, who's that?

708
00:44:57,361 --> 00:44:58,362
Who is it?

709
00:45:01,990 --> 00:45:03,075
Ms. Yoon…

710
00:45:11,208 --> 00:45:12,292
[Eun-jung] The military?

711
00:45:13,043 --> 00:45:16,338
Yeah. He and my dad had an argument.

712
00:45:19,007 --> 00:45:21,427
My dad hit him hard.

713
00:45:22,428 --> 00:45:24,221
- He did?
- Yeah.

714
00:45:25,180 --> 00:45:27,224
He said he should've gone a while ago.

715
00:45:27,307 --> 00:45:28,308
When's he going?

716
00:45:30,310 --> 00:45:31,145
[door opens]

717
00:45:32,229 --> 00:45:33,230
[Sang-yeon clears throat]

718
00:45:40,946 --> 00:45:42,281
The seventh, next month.

719
00:45:43,073 --> 00:45:45,993
What? That's barely two weeks from now.

720
00:45:46,076 --> 00:45:47,161
I know.

721
00:45:48,454 --> 00:45:49,371
[Eun-jung sighs]

722
00:45:50,038 --> 00:45:52,166
But do you wanna hear some good news?

723
00:45:52,750 --> 00:45:53,584
Mm-hmm.

724
00:45:53,667 --> 00:45:56,670
<i>Oppa</i>… and his girlfriend ended things.

725
00:45:57,296 --> 00:45:58,964
- They broke up?
- Yeah.

726
00:45:59,465 --> 00:46:01,049
- Oh.
- My mom didn't like her.

727
00:46:02,384 --> 00:46:03,594
Wanna see something?

728
00:46:04,344 --> 00:46:05,179
What?

729
00:46:10,267 --> 00:46:11,226
[Sang-yeon] Oh.

730
00:46:12,811 --> 00:46:14,021
Here it is.

731
00:46:14,104 --> 00:46:15,314
What is that?

732
00:46:16,565 --> 00:46:17,858
It's his diary.

733
00:46:23,655 --> 00:46:25,741
[pensive music playing]

734
00:46:25,824 --> 00:46:27,743
[Sang-hak] <i>I'm joining the military.</i>

735
00:46:29,369 --> 00:46:31,914
<i>You might say that it's a stupid decision,</i>

736
00:46:32,998 --> 00:46:37,294
<i>but let's just say</i>
<i>it represents my willpower.</i>

737
00:46:39,505 --> 00:46:42,049
<i>I'm… going to run.</i>

738
00:46:43,675 --> 00:46:44,968
<i>Far away from you.</i>

739
00:46:46,261 --> 00:46:48,597
